import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['u'], data['v'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between u and v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['u'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['u'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['u'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['u'].median():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of u?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist2d(data['u'], data['v'], bins=20, cmap=plt.cm.Blues)
    plt.title('What is the joint distribution of u and v?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    cbar = plt.colorbar()
    cbar.ax.set_ylabel('Counts')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['u'], alpha=0.5, label='u')
    ax.hist(data['v'], alpha=0.5, label='v')
    ax.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='u mean')
    ax.axvline(data['v'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='v mean')
    ax.axvline(data['u'].std(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='u std')
    ax.axvline(data['v'].std(), color='orange', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='v std')
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the mean and standard deviation of u and v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
